                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430227-988-offence-1 t18430227-name-906"></join>Charles Oldfield</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-907" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-907" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-907" type="surname" value="WOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-907" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES WOOD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am clerk to Charles Oldfield, a builder. On the 21st of Jan. I missed two wheelbarrows from his yard in Sussex-square, Padding<lb></lb>ton—I found them on the 27th, on a piece of waste ground at the back of Charles-street, Paddington—the prisoner was not using them at the time—he said he had borrowed them of Rayner, who was acting as foreman to Mr. Oldfield.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I had them between two and three months. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> He might have had them three weeks, but not longer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-908" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-908" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-908" type="surname" value="RAYNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-908" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES RAYNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I did not lend the prisoner any barrows in Nov., Dec., or Jan.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> Two months ago he was drinking with me in a public-house, and he said, "Are those barrows safe"—I said, "Yes"—he said, "Very well, we are going to begin again"—I said, "Very well, when you want them I will send them"—that was in a public-house in Bathurst-street, and he asked me if I had a sieve—I said, "No"—he said they had lost two sieves—an<lb></lb>other of the men came to me on the Thursday following, and told me to send the barrows home, which I did by a man, and he did not return them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-909" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-909" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-909" type="surname" value="WIBLIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-909" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT WIBLIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I was at work with the prisoner in Jan.—I saw the wheelbarrows—he said he would sell them to me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did not you tell me that I could come to work with you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, and you offered to sell me the barrows for 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I said I would let you know in the morning, but I had some new ones come in, and did not want them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-910" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-910" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-910" type="surname" value="CLARIDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-910" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM CLARIDGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a labourer. I hired these barrows of the prisoner about six weeks ago—he did not say anything to me about selling them, but I was in want of two, and he said he had two—I had them two days, and they were then taken from me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> Wiblin got on the work, and he wanted to get me away—it is all malice his coming against me—I was told by two or three of his men to mind what I was about as he would get me off.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-911" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-911" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-911" type="surname" value="WIBLIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-911" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT WIBLIN</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I have not the least animosity against the prisoner—I have taken his boy since he has been here, and I had my tool-house broken open and my shovel stolen—the prisoner wanted me to brand the barrows with my iron.</p>
